# Database & EF Core 9 Conventions

## Naming

- Snake_case in DB, PascalCase in C# — via `EFCore.NamingConventions` package.
- Migration name → `yyyyMMddHHmm_VerbNoun` (e.g. `202605091200_AddReportSlaColumns`).

## AuditableEntity (mandatory for every entity)

```csharp
public abstract class AuditableEntity
{
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public Guid? CreatedBy { get; set; }
    public DateTime? UpdatedAt { get; set; }
    public Guid? UpdatedBy { get; set; }
}
```

Populated by `AuditableEntityInterceptor` reading `ICurrentUser` + `IDateTime`.

## Soft delete (User, Report, Comment)

- `DeletedAt` nullable column.
- Global query filter: `modelBuilder.Entity<Report>().HasQueryFilter(r => r.DeletedAt == null);`
- BR-AUTH-022: Account hard-deleted after 90 days; user reports become `Anonymized`.

## Geo (PostGIS)

```csharp
// Domain
public Point Location { get; private set; }   // NetTopologySuite.Geometries

// Configuration
builder.Property(r => r.Location)
    .HasColumnType("geometry(Point, 4326)")
    .IsRequired();
builder.HasIndex(r => r.Location).HasMethod("GIST");
```

## Required indexes

| Table | Columns | Type |
|-------|---------|------|
| Report | `(Status, CreatedAt)` | btree |
| Report | `Location` | GIST |
| User   | `Email` | unique |
| User   | `PhoneNumber` | unique |

## Transaction boundary

- ONE `SaveChangesAsync` per request — owned by `TransactionBehavior` or `IUnitOfWork`.
- Never call `SaveChangesAsync` inside loops or repository methods.

## Query patterns

```csharp
// ✅ Projection, no tracking, paginated
var items = await db.Reports
    .Where(r => r.Status == ReportStatus.Submitted)
    .OrderByDescending(r => r.CreatedAt)
    .Skip((page - 1) * pageSize).Take(pageSize)
    .ProjectToType<ReportDto>()             // Mapster
    .ToListAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);

// ❌ N+1 / over-fetching
var reports = await db.Reports.ToListAsync(ct);
foreach (var r in reports) {
    var media = await db.Media.Where(m => m.ReportId == r.Id).ToListAsync(ct);
}
```

## Migrations in production

- Dev → migrate at startup is OK.
- Staging/Prod → `dotnet ef migrations bundle` or external tool. **Never** auto-migrate at startup in prod.
- Never delete a merged migration. Add a new revert migration instead.

## Duplicate detection (BR-REP-030)

```sql
-- Same category + within 50m + within 24h
ST_DWithin(r1.location::geography, r2.location::geography, 50)
  AND r1.pollution_type = r2.pollution_type
  AND r2.created_at >= r1.created_at - INTERVAL '24 hours'
```
